parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical Fire and Wiring Harness Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical fires can cause damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. Wiring harness failure can also lead to loss of vehicle control, stalling, or shutdown.
symptoms: loss of power to headlights or power steering
sparks or flames from the ignition switch or distributor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition switch failure can cause the vehicle to shut down or catch fire, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke coming from the ignition switch

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Vehicle stalling and shutting down can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds.
The crossflow of fuel between tanks can cause overflow, leading to fuel spillage on the ground, which can result in fires or explosions.
symptoms: Fuel siphons from one tank to another
fuel pours from one tank into another
excessive fuel leakage onto the ground.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the check valve can cause fuel to flow between tanks, leading to overflow and fuel spillage, which can result in fires or explosions.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from one tank to another
fuel pours from one tank into another
excessive fuel leakage onto the ground.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank straps can cause the tank to fall, leading to fuel leakage and potentially causing fires or explosions.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Fuel Tank Rust and Leakage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting of the rear fuel tank can cause fuel leakage, which can result in fires or explosions.
The defective design of the fuel tank can cause fuel leakage, which can result in fires or explosions.
The failure of the fuel pressure regulator can cause fuel leakage, which can result in fires or explosions.
The fuel tank can catch fire, resulting in a vehicle fire, which can cause injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Flames coming from the fuel tank

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The repeated failure of the door handle can cause inconvenience and potentially lead to safety issues if the driver is unable to exit the vehicle quickly in an emergency situation.
symptoms: the door handle does not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature fading and peeling of paint can lead to corrosion, which can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle and create safety risks.
symptoms: The paint is fading or peeling
rust is visible on the frame rails and cross members
corrosion is evident on the chassis.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch washer and booster unit can cause the clutch pedal to malfunction, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Hood Hydraulic Cylinder Support Rod Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine hood hydraulic cylinder support rod can cause the hood to suddenly descend, obstructing the driver's view and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The engine hood does not stay up
the engine hood hydraulic cylinder support rod is broken.
